<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<transcript>
<text start="0.00" dur="3.50">Welcome back to Binging with Babish.</text>
<text start="3.50" dur="4.20">Today we are making <font color="#E5E5E5">pasta aglio e olio</font>,</text>
<text start="7.70" dur="3.80">arguably one of the greatest pasta dishes ever conceived.</text>
<text start="11.50" dur="4.50">Four humble ingredients: spaghetti, garlic, olive oil, and red pepper flakes.</text>
<text start="16.00" dur="3.20">Start by bringing a large pot of heavily salted water to a boil.</text>
<text start="19.20" dur="4.00">Slice eight cloves of garlic as thinly as possible.</text>
<text start="23.20" dur="3.50">Heat a third of a cup of olive oil over medium-low heat.</text>
<text start="26.70" dur="4.20">Add the garlic and cook until lightly golden, stirring frequently.</text>
<text start="30.90" dur="3.80">Add half a teaspoon of red pepper flakes and cook one minute more.</text>
<text start="34.70" dur="4.50">Add a ladle of starchy pasta water and cook until the sauce emulsifies.</text>
<text start="39.20" dur="3.00">Drain pasta al dente and add directly to the pan.</text>
<text start="42.20" dur="4.20">Toss vigorously, adding more pasta water as needed to create a silky sauce.</text>
<text start="46.40" dur="3.50">Finish with fresh parsley and serve immediately. That&#39;s it.</text>
</transcript>
